The paper deals with discrete Voronoi games, which are a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the concept of weak $\epsilon$-nets, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and has applications in approximation algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves game theory (cs.GT) as it studies the strategies of two players in the Voronoi game.
